You have to provide a list of runtimes to use.

The default runtime will be 'runtimes/node', but it can be overwritten using the --runtime flag.

When compiling inside a docker image, the runtime to use will be autocalculated based on the platform to build for and the flavor.

For example, executing:

blacksmith compile --docker-image-id alpine-image --flavor alpine --platform linux-x64 zlib

The search path for runtimes will be:

runtimes/linux-x64/alpine/node, runtimes/linux-x64/node, runtimes/node

